# Target USB-C Port Configuration Example
#
# This file identifies the USB-C port to use for networking.
#
# Choose ONE of the two detection methods below and uncomment the relevant section.
# See docs/how-to-select-port.md for detailed instructions on finding these values.

#############################################################################
# METHOD 1: sysfs-based detection (systems with /sys/class/typec/ support)
#############################################################################
#
# Use this method if your system has Type-C subsystem support.
# Pros: Detects connection state changes, power delivery info, orientation
# Cons: Requires CONFIG_TYPEC kernel support
#
# DETECTION_METHOD=sysfs
# TYPEC_PORT=port0
# TYPEC_PORT_PATH=/sys/class/typec/port0
# TYPEC_DATA_ROLE=host
# TYPEC_POWER_ROLE=source
# TYPEC_ORIENTATION=normal
# USB_CONTROLLER=xhci_hcd


#############################################################################
# METHOD 2: libusb-based detection (systems without sysfs support)
#############################################################################
#
# Use this method on systems without /sys/class/typec/ support.
# Requires identifying your USB device via 'lsusb' command.
#
# Pros: Works on systems without Type-C sysfs
# Cons: Device numbers may change on reconnection
#
# To find these values:
#   1. Connect your USB device to the target port
#   2. Run: lsusb
#   3. Identify your device (Bus and Device numbers)
#   4. Fill in the values below
#
# Example output:
#   Bus 002 Device 004: ID 1234:5678 Example Device
#   ^^^           ^^^        ^^^^:^^^^
#   BUS        DEVICE      VENDOR:PRODUCT
#
# DETECTION_METHOD=libusb
# USB_BUS=002
# USB_DEVICE=004
# USB_SPEED=5000
# USB_VENDOR_PRODUCT=1234:5678
# USB_DESCRIPTION="Example USB Device"
# USB_DEVICE_PATH=/dev/bus/usb/002/004


#############################################################################
# INSTRUCTIONS
#############################################################################
#
# 1. Choose your detection method (sysfs or libusb)
# 2. Uncomment ALL lines in the corresponding section
# 3. Fill in the correct values for your system
# 4. Save this file as: target_usb_c_port.env (remove the .example)
#
# You can verify the configuration by running:
#   source target_usb_c_port.env
#   echo "Detection method: $DETECTION_METHOD"
#   echo "USB device path: $USB_DEVICE_PATH"
#
# For detailed instructions, see: docs/how-to-select-port.md
